# Managed by myplace (chezmoi). bat's config file is a list of command-line
# arguments, one per line. bat is installed via mise on every machine.
# Docs: https://github.com/sharkdp/bat#configuration-file

# Theme. bat 0.25+ bundles the Catppuccin family, so no theme files or
# `bat cache --build` are needed. "auto" detects the terminal background and
# picks the dark/light variant below — Mocha in the dark, Latte in the light,
# matching the system light/dark setup (same flavors as Zed). Detection falls
# back to the dark theme over SSH and in pipes, which is what we want.
--theme="auto"
--theme-dark="Catppuccin Mocha"
--theme-light="Catppuccin Latte"

# Line numbers, git-modification markers, and a filename header — no heavy grid.
--style="numbers,changes,header"

# Page only when writing to a terminal, so piped/agent output stays plain.
--paging=auto
